HEADWORD: Aspersed
<hw>As*persed"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Having an indefinite number of small charges
scattered or strewed over the surface.</def>
<rj><au>Cussans.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Bespattered; slandered; calumniated.</def>
<rj><au>Motley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Asperser</ent>⟦br⟧
